ent\n- Lines 295-298: Evaluation duration is measured and recorded in metrics\n\nA similar pattern is implemented for recording rules in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/recording_rule.go:Eval()` (line 113-127) and `recordingRule.Run()` (line 139-169).\n\n## Time Budget Analysis\nThe overrun occurs when an evaluation takes longer than the base tick interval. The scheduler detects this by attempting to queue the next evaluation while the previous one is still being processed. If the channel still contains an unprocessed message, it indicates the evaluation is exceeding its time budget, resulting in the warning log and incrementing the `grafana_alerting_schedule_rule_evaluations_missed_total` metric."
